          "body": "## Context\n\nApply the workspace static-testing integration process to this repo:\n\n- `/workspaces/ocr-container/docs/process/static-testing.md`\n\nThe important rollout rule is advisory first: add the new scanner targets and visibility without blocking `make ci` initially. After the first few scans, file/fix issues for real findings, document accepted deviations, then graduate the targets into blocking `static-check` / `ci`.\n\n## Manual scan baseline from 2026-05-22\n\nCommands were run manually against `pd-book-tools` without changing the repo.\n\n- `zizmor 1.25.2 .github/workflows`: findings, exit 14.\n  - High-confidence unpinned action refs in `ci.yml` and `release.yml`.\n  - `actions/checkout` steps missing `persist-credentials: false`.\n  - High-confidence template injection in `release.yml` using `${{ github.ref_name }}` inside a shell `run:` block.\n  - Low-confidence cache-poisoning warning for `astral-sh/setup-uv` in release workflow.\n  - Informational suggestion to replace `softprops/action-gh-release` with `gh release`.\n- `actionlint 1.7.12 .github/workflows/*.yml`: clean.\n- `trivy 0.70.0 fs --scanners vuln,misconfig,secret .`: one medium dependency vuln from `uv.lock`.\n  - `idna 3.13`, `CVE-2026-45409`, fixed in `3.15`.\n- `gitleaks 8.30.1 detect`: clean for both filesystem and git-history scans.\n- `shellcheck 0.11.0 scripts/do-release.sh`: clean.\n- `hadolint`: not applicable; no Dockerfile found.\n- OpenSSF Scorecard: not completed locally because unauthenticated GitHub API rate limiting caused a long wait. Treat as GitHub-side advisory later.\n- CodeQL: not run locally; better enabled as GitHub code scanning later.\n\nOSV-Scanner was also tried but does not read this repo's `uv.lock` directly. It required `uv export` and still emitted an internal resolution error while reporting the same `idna` vulnerability. Prefer Trivy for this repo.\n\n## Scope\n\nAdd advisory static-testing integration for this repo. Do not make the new tools block `make ci` in the first implementation unless the scan is clean and the baseline is explicitly accepted in the same PR.\n\nExpected repo targets:\n\n- `dependency-scan`: Trivy vulnerability scan for dependency manifests/lockfiles.\n- `security-scan`: gitleaks plus dependency scan, initially advisory/non-blocking.\n- `workflow-lint`: zizmor plus actionlint, initially advisory/non-blocking.\n- `trivy-scan`: broader Trivy scan, advisory by default.\n- `static-check`: aggregate target that can eventually become the blocking static gate before tests/build.\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n\n- Makefile exposes advisory targets for dependency/security/workflow scanning.\n- GitHub Actions or scheduled/manual workflow gives visibility into advisory scan results without blocking normal PRs at first.\n- The `idna` vulnerability is tracked as a cleanup item or fixed in the same rollout if low-risk.\n- The `zizmor` workflow findings are tracked as cleanup items or fixed in the same rollout if low-risk.\n- The PR documents which checks remain advisory and what must be true before they become blocking.\n- After cleanup/baseline, a follow-up can remove advisory wrappers and wire the relevant targets into `static-check` and `ci`.\n\n## Notes\n\nTreat this as a staged hardening task, not a one-shot CI gate. The goal is to get recurring signal first, then make the signal blocking once the repo has a clean or documented baseline.\n",
